        detailed_explanation "Secure configuration involves implementing and maintaining security settings
            +b that protect systems from unauthorized access and vulnerabilities. In the
            +b context of a Secure Development Lifecycle (SDL), it is crucial to perform
            +b structured analyses that incorporate threat modeling, such as STRIDE, to
            +b identify potential security threats early in the development process. Threat
            +b modeling is a proactive approach that helps developers understand how an
            +b attacker might compromise their system, allowing them to make informed design
            +b choices to mitigate risks. By integrating these analyses into the SDL,
            +b organizations can ensure that security is considered at every stage of
            +b development, reducing the likelihood of vulnerabilities in the final product."
